records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tyler J Lewein in court with attorney Kelsey Morin.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1 of the Amended Information.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Victims give statements.  Defendant's employer gives statement on behalf of defendant.  Court denies expungement.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

28 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - none)
  -  14 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  14 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  business, victim/witnesses or co-actor listed in the Complaint.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

RESTITUTION:  to be determined

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DRGOD:  $10.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 9 months -  First 4 months straight time; second 5 months with release for work and treatment, stayed for use at agent's discretion if accepted into drug treatment court.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  Remanded into the custody of the Sheriff's Department.  

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.  Restitution hearing scheduled for December 7, 2016 at 03:00 pm.
